<STARTDOC>
macro(colsline(skip)(from)(to))
 (Sets a horizontal line over some columns in a row, skipping an initial
tt(skip) number of columns. This macro does em(not) define a row by itself but
tt(colsline) calls must be the (only) argument(s) of a tt(row) macro. To write
a line across the table's full width use tt(rowline). The arguments specify
the number of columns to skip, the column number where the horizontal line
should start and the column number where the horizontal line should end. It is
the responsibility of the author to ensure that the arguments are sensible. To
set horizontal lines across columns 1 until 2 and columns 4 until 5 table of a
table use:
        verb(
    row(colsline(0)(1)(2)colsline(1)(4)(5))
        )
)
<>
DEFINEMACRO(colsline)(3)(\
    PUSHCOUNTER(XXone)(ARG3)\
<html xml>
    XXifnzero(ARG1)(NOTRANS(<td colspan=ARG1></td>))\
    ADDTOCOUNTER(XXone)(-ARG2)\
    ADDTOCOUNTER(XXone)(1)\
    NOTRANS(<td colspan=)\
    COUNTERVALUE(XXone)\
    NOTRANS(><hr></td>)\
<latex>
    NOTRANS( \cline{)\
    ARG2-ARG3\
    +CHAR(})\
<man ms>
    SETCOUNTER(XXsawcolsline)(1)\
    SETCOUNTER(XXsawalign)(1)\
    XXifnzero(ARG1)(addntosymbol(XXtablealign)(ARG1)(c))\
    ADDTOCOUNTER(XXone)(-ARG2)\
    ADDTOCOUNTER(XXone)(1)\
    addntosymbol(XXtablealign)(XXone)(+NOTRANS(-))\
<else>
    XXnl()\
<>
    POPCOUNTER(XXone)\
)
